      <hedline>
        <hl1>Multiple-Party Ballot Rejected in Primaries</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Supreme Court invalidated California's blanket primary, in which voters can cast ballots for candidates of any party. The 7-to-2 decision also cast serious doubt on the more common open primary, which allows voters in more than half the states to request a particular party's ballot. Article, Page A19.</p>
